        },
        {
            "_id": "oBwbVGDH9G0p3y9n",
            "img": "systems/sf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Stabilization Ring",
            "sort": 400000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "interaction",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>An anchored dimensional is a creature from between realities forced to adopt a physical, three-dimensional form via a magitech device called a stabilization ring. The stabilization ring uses the anchored dimensional's AC and saving throws, but it has hardness 3, HP 20 (BT 10). When the stabilization ring is broken, the anchored dimensional gains concealment. When the stabilization ring is destroyed, the dimensional is freed, returning home to the incomprehensible space between realities.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": []
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "XPCkoxOB1keStlw5",
            "img": "systems/sf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Frenetic Thrash",
            "sort": 500000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 3
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The anchored dimensional lashes out in all directions, making a spined lash Strike against each adjacent enemy. Each attack counts toward their multiple attack penalty, but they don't increase their penalty until all these attacks have been made.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
